title: Small dodecicosidodecahedron
summary: In geometry, the small dodecicosidodecahedron (or small dodekicosidodecahedron) is a nonconvex uniform polyhedron, indexed as U33. It has 44 faces (20 triangles, 12 pentagons, and 12 decagons), 120 edges, and 60 vertices.[1] Its vertex figure is a crossed quadrilateral.
